        {
            "_id": "AtCXVdtehljc8QdT",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Reactive Detach",
            "sort": 1100000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "reaction"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The sarcovalt takes slashing damage from a creature while they have another creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed] or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained]</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The sarcovalt uses Detach Head. Their head keeps the other creature grabbed or restrained, and their body Steps. The sarcovalt gains resistance 5 to the triggering slashing damage.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Reactive Detach]</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "xBRFeBqx4UcT38rV",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Return to Sender",
            "sort": 1200000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "reaction"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature escapes from being @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed] or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained] by the sarcovalt's detached head</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The sarcovalt's head returns to their body via the shortest possible path. Any creature in a straight line between the head and the body must succeed at a @Check[reflex|dc:21] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} for 1 round (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} on a critical failure). The sarcovalt Dismisses Detach Head.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "FO3rk85tKmhFRdrU",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Detach Head",
            "sort": 1300000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "free"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The sarcovalt takes damage from a critical hit with a slashing weapon or has their head removed (such as by a vorpal weapon)</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The sarcovalt can survive decapitation and isn't killed if an effect that removes their head would kill them. Instead, the sarcovalt's head becomes detached from their body. The detached head has the same statistics as the body (except for the aura of blight) and gains the minion trait. The sarcovalt's body can issue a verbal command to the detached head as a single action, giving the head 2 actions. The detached head and body share the same pool of Hit Points.</p>\n<p>While their head is detached, the sarcovalt's body can't make beak Strikes or use Malodorous Shriek. The detached head can only Climb, Fly, Stride, make beak Strikes, or use Malodorous Shriek.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "occult"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "KWvn4JKkgo0whAiV",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Malodorous Shriek",
            "sort": 1400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The sarcovalt screeches through their skull (detached or not), spraying whatever festering viscera remains in their head in a @Template[type:cone|distance:20]. Each creature in the area takes @Damage[3d6[sonic],3d6[poison]|options:area-damage] damage (@Check[reflex|dc:21|basic] save). The sarcovalt can't use this ability again for [[/br 1d4 #Recharge this ability]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "occult",
